definitions.definition: The fruit of the date palm , Phoenix dactylifera , somewhat in the shape of an olive , containing a soft, sweet pulp and enclosing a hard kernel. [from 14th c.]
examples: We made a nice cake from dates .
There were a few dates planted around the house.

definitions.definition: ( Australia , New Zealand ) The anus . [from 20th c.]

main_definition: The fruit of the date palm , Phoenix dactylifera , somewhat in the shape of an olive , containing a soft, sweet pulp and enclosing a hard kernel. [from 14th c.]
secondary_definitions: ( Australia , New Zealand ) The anus . [from 20th c.]

definitions.definition: The addition to a writing , inscription , coin , etc., which specifies the time (especially the day, month, and year) when the writing or inscription was given, executed, or made.
examples: the date of a letter, of a will, of a deed, of a coin, etc.
US date : 05/24/08 = Tuesday, May 24th, 2008. UK date : 24/05/08 = Tuesday 24th May 2008.

definitions.definition: A specific day in time at which a transaction or event takes place, or is appointed to take place; a given point of time.
examples: Do you know the date of the wedding?
We had to change the dates of the festival because of the flooding.
You may need that at a later date .

definitions.definition: A given or assigned length of life ; duration .

examples: I arranged a date with my Australian business partners.

definitions.definition: One's companion for social activities or occasions, especially a romantic partner.
examples: I brought Melinda to the wedding as my date .

definitions.definition: A romantic meeting or outing with a lover or potential lover, or the person so met.
examples: We really hit it off on the first date , so we decided to meet the week after.
The cinema is a popular place to take someone on a date .
